'''''Black Lightning''''' is an extant<ref>[http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.1578/default.html The Library of Congress American Silent Feature Film Survival Catalog: ''Black Lightning'']</ref> 1924 American silent drama film directed by [[James P. Hogan (director)|James P. Hogan]], and starring [[Clara Bow]] and a dog named Thunder. It was made by independent [[Gotham Pictures]].<ref>[http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/DetailView.aspx?s=&Movie=2886 The AFI Catalog of Feature Films:''Black Lightning'']</ref> Prints of the film are held at the Russian state film archive [[Gosfilmofond]] and the [[UCLA Film and Television Archive]].

==Cast==
*[[Clara Bow]] - Martha Larned
*Harold Austin - Roy Chambers
*[[Eddie Phillips (actor)|Eddie Phillips]] - Ez Howard
*Joe Butterworth - Larned/ Dick
*Thunder the Dog - Thunder
*[[Mark Fenton]] - Doctor
*John Pringle - City Doctor (*John Pringle was the father of actor [[John Gilbert (actor)|John Gilbert]])
*James P. Hogan - Frank Larned
*[[James Mason (American actor)|Jim Mason]] - Jim Howard

